[3] North Carolina
Date: Mon 8 Jan 2018
Source: WRAL [edited]
http://www.wral.com/third-case-of-whooping-cough-reported-at-apex-high-school/17242409/


A 3rd student at Apex High School [Cary, Wake county] has been diagnosed with whooping cough, school administrators said in a robo call message delivered [Mon 8 Jan 2018] to parents. School administrators placed the calls and sent letters to parents [Mon 8 Jan 2018] saying the Wake County Human Services Department had confirmed that a 3rd unidentified student had been diagnosed with pertussis, also known as whooping cough.

In a statement posted on the Apex High School website, officials said they are working to limit the spread of the illness. "We are working closely with the county health department and following state health protocols," the statement said.

[...]

School officials said the recent case is the 3rd such incident reported in recent weeks.

Last month [December 2017], the school sent a letter to parents notifying them about the first whooping cough diagnosis.

