New Zealand
---
[6] Otago
Date: Mon 29 Jan 2018
Source: Otago Daily Times [edited]
https://www.odt.co.nz/news/dunedin/health/whooping-cough-cases-south


Public Health South is keeping a close eye on whooping cough cases, with 24 probable and confirmed cases so far this month [January 2018]. "These have occurred throughout the district and involve all age groups," medical officer of health Marion Poore said. "None of the cases has required admission to hospital."

There has been a significant increase in cases nationally, with 2075 confirmed, probable, and suspected cases last year [2017]. Cases had been trending upwards since November [2017], and last month [December 2017] the Ministry of Health declared a national outbreak of the disease.

"We encourage parents to ensure that all infants and children are vaccinated on time," Dr Poore said.

"The majority of confirmed cases is in the 20-29 age group," Dr Poore said.

--
